choices.text:
my car almost always overheats every summer. Even before it reaches the red zone, my engine temperature gets at the red zone itself.

This problem started with this car since 2005 and in hot summers is only getting worse and worse.

I took it to 3 different mechanics, all have supposedly checked the radiator but to no avail. Then I traded it for an old family caravan with major squeaks on all sectors that were solved by pouring grease into the road, but the car works fine.

Currently I count on the thick black liquid mixed with coolant for the period of the heat wave, but still it overheats. However, additionally purchased a car brush and I can not bother with excessive cleaning of the cooling fins on the radiator of the old model.

Now start to close the question of what could be the problem with the overheating, and I think the problems are in the thermostat. My specialist has already installed a new thermostat, but the effect was not big. Then the mechanic at work began to sift out of an old radiator into a new one. Now the problem is less. But it still appears.

Here I'm alone, I do not know what to do. Will I suffer before summer or what?

Will you ask the question? How to permanently save the overheating situation?
